# Server Architecture

Three-layer pattern: **Model → Controller → Router**. Types live in `src/server/types/<domain>/`.

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Location | Role |
|-------|----------|------|
| Types | `src/server/types/<domain>/index.ts` | Zod schemas + inferred TS types, re-exports DB types |
| Model | `src/server/models/<Domain>Model.ts` | Raw DB queries only, uses `db` singleton |
| Controller | `src/server/controllers/<Domain>Controller.ts` | Business logic, calls model static methods |
| Router | `src/server/trpc/routers/<domain>.ts` | Thin wire-up, calls controller with values from `ctx` |

## Classes

Both models and controllers are **abstract classes with public static methods**. No constructors, no instances.

```ts
// ✅ Model — uses db singleton, no ctx
export abstract class ProfileModel {
  public static async get(id: string): Promise<ProfileRow | null> {
    return db.selectFrom("profiles").selectAll().where("id", "=", id).executeTakeFirst() ?? null;
  }
  public static async getMany(limit: number) { ... }
  public static async create(data: { id: string; email: string | null }) { ... }
  public static async upsert(data: ...) { ... }
  public static async delete(id: string) { ... }
}

// ✅ Controller — calls model, takes explicit primitive args (not ctx)
export abstract class ProfileController {
  public static async getMe(userId: string) {
    return ProfileModel.get(userId);
  }
  public static async upsert(userId: string, email: string | null, input: UpsertProfileInput) {
    return ProfileModel.upsert({ id: userId, email, ...input });
  }
}

// ✅ Router — one-liners, passes values from ctx explicitly
export const profileRouter = createTRPCRouter({
  me: protectedProcedure.query(({ ctx }) => ProfileController.getMe(ctx.user.id)),
  upsert: protectedProcedure.input(upsertProfileInput).mutation(({ ctx, input }) =>
    ProfileController.upsert(ctx.user.id, ctx.user.email ?? null, input)
  ),
});
```

## Every model must have

`get`, `getMany`, `create`, `upsert`, `delete` as a baseline — add domain-specific methods on top.

## Exports

Each layer has a barrel `index.ts` that re-exports its classes:
- `src/server/models/index.ts` → `export * from "./ProfileModel"`
- `src/server/controllers/index.ts` → `export * from "./ProfileController"`
- `src/server/types/index.ts` → `export * from "./<domain>/index"`
